-- Spain’s Valencia Region to Cut Up to 50% of Staff, Mundo Reports
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-04-22T10:20:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/spain-s-valencia-region-to-cut-up-to-50-of-staff-mundo-reports.html
The Spanish region of Valencia
plans to cut 40 percent to 50 percent of its almost 11,000
public workers to save money, the area’s Vice President Jose
Ciscar said in an interview with  El Mundo .  Along with the “significant” job reduction plan, the
regional government will transform the 43 public companies and
entities into six big groups, Ciscar said, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
